orleans 
the levees and big pumps keep the saucershaped new orleans area 
dry at its highest point new orleans is about 14 feet above sea 
level much of it is below sea level 
exactly 23 years ago hurricane betsy pushed a storm surge over 
levees and flooded the eastern end of new orleans killing 70 
people in louisiana and causing 11 billion in damages 
we have a more improved levee system and hurricane protection 
system than we had 20 years ago said plaquemines parish 
