<TEXT>
here is the text of the democratic response to 
president reagans radio address saturday given by sen robert c 
byrd dwva 
this week millions of american children went back to school 
these young people represent americas future 
today i want to take issue with what the president has been 
saying about education lets set the record straight 
for seven years now the congress and the administration have 
been working on our arithmetic the administration subtracts from 
education the congress adds to save it 
for seven years now we democrats have been trying to educate the 
administration about the value of education it hasnt helped 
im not surprised this white house has never had a real 
commitment to excellence in education i dont understand why the 
administration hasnt done its homework 
americas future economic prosperity depends on having the best 
educated workforce in the world put simply an educated america is 
a strong america 
just two days ago the council on competitiveness stated that 
america is developing an ominous dependence on foreign 
professors and researchers forty percent of all engineering 
students graduating from american colleges and universities are now 
foreignborn we now import brains and intellectual talent the same 
way that we import cars and radios 
why do we rely so heavily on foreign talent because our schools 
are not teaching our children the math and science skills they need 
for our new hightech economy and thats not all according to a 
recent survey 75 percent of all american students could not locate 
the persian gulf on a world map 
the alarm has been sounded again and again yet nothing has been 
done by the white house to link americas economic future to 
rebuilding our nations educational system nothing at all 
this white house talks a lot about the three rs but when it 
comes to helping education their three rs amount to rhetoric 
reductions and retrenchment 
if the white house had its way pell grants would be cut by 40 
percent college work study programs would end vocational 
education would stop altogether and aid to graduate school 
students would come to a halt even the drug free school 
program would be cut by 50 percent 
my friends this is terribly wrong 
it used to be that a highschool diploma was the guarantee of a 
good job and the chance to marry and settle down now even our 
high school graduates are struggling put simply you cant get 
ahead unless you have the best education possible 
but getting a good college education is almost out of reach for 
these young americans and for millions of other americans 
there are hundreds of thousands of middleclass families 
struggling to make ends meet so they can send their children to 
college they want their children to get ahead to be a part of an 
american dream 
but in the last seven years their sacrifice has gone unrewarded 
even though college tuitions have risen by 60 percent since 1981 
again and again the administration has tried to cut student aid i 
have had to vote 14 times in the last seven years to protect 
student loan programs fourteen times 
and when it comes to doing something about adult illiteracy 
the white house blackboard is completely blank twentythree 
million americans are now functionally illiterate how difficult it 
must be to live a life when you cannot read and write when you 
cannot read the bible or a story to your children or even the 
funny pages in the newspaper 
yet these illiterate americans are the very americans who can 
make the difference if america is to stay no 1 if we want 
america to be strong in every way we need to recognize that smart 
students are just as important as smart weapons in my home state 
of west virginia the students who answered my annual survey know 
that too forty percent of them rated education as the first 
priority of the federal government 
we need leadership in the white house that appreciates the value 
of education as much as do the young people of west virginia 
i am encouraged that at least one of the presidential candidates 
has made a pledge that no college student should be turned away 
from college because they cant get financial aid 
the education formula for americas future prosperity is clear 
good schools equal a smart workforce and that adds up to an america 
that is still the best 
lets do our homework now so we dont flunk later in this 
course america cant afford to fail 
thank you and may god bless you 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

