<TEXT>
a millionaire grandfather landed a 
330pound airplane in his homeland saturday after a 23day flight 
from britain that set a record for ultralight aviation 
vijaypat singhanias ultralight plane made a perfect landing at 
new delhis safdarjung airport at 1110 am singhania 49 took 
off from biggin hill in kent on aug 18 
the redandwhite fiberglass aircraft flew 6000 miles through 
high winds and sandstorms and over hundreds of miles of open sea 
singhania said he fought depression heat sores and a steady weight 
loss in the hours spent in the cramped cockpit of the coneshaped 
plane 
the 21feet long plane has a onehalfhorsepower engine and a 
wingspan of 32 feet its top speed is about 60 mph 
flying at 10000 feet over the mediterranean i saw ships and 
tried to visualize how long it would take for them to pick me up if 
i fell in the bespectacled balding industrialist said at the 
airport 
i had a lifejacket strapped on shark repellent by my side and 
kept talking to my granddaughters picture that was strapped on to 
the front of my cockpit to keep myself from going crazy 
he said he lost 24 pounds during the trip 
singhania the head of indias thirdlargest business group 
beat a 34day speed record set over the same course this year by a 
british television journalist brian milton 
milton was in new delhi to greet singhania at the end of the 
flight 
there have been only five long flights above 5000 miles 
undertaken in a microlight aircraft he said anyone who 
attempts such a flight will have to beat vijay to make the record 
the plane is named lespirit dindian post after a bombaybased 
newspaper owned by the singhania group singhania said the name was 
a combination of his two passions the spirit of adventure and 
his newspaper 
i wanted to try and break the record i wanted to be an 
ambassador for my country and show people india is not just a 
country of snake charmers he said 
i am very proud to have established india on the aviation map 
and feel tremendously thrilled that i managed to so positively 
portray the indomitable spirit latent in all men the spirit of 
adventure singhania said 
and not least of all i was running out of stories to tell my 
grandchildren now i have a fund of tales 
</TEXT>
