and ignored by ronald reagan the presidential yacht sequoia is on 
the last leg of a 120city fundraising tour before it is returned 
to white house control 
the sequoia was bought by the commerce department from a 
philadelphia family in 1929 after hoover wintered on the boat in 
florida in 1933 it was acquired by the navy and declared the 
official presidential yacht 
the 105foot vessel served eight presidents over a period of 44 
years before carter ordered the ship sold at auction in 1977 as an 
austerity move 
the sequoia is really a symbol of the presidency in the 20th 
century said j michael mcgehee spokesman for the presidential 
yacht trust the private group that bought the ship and began 
restoring it in 1981 
franklin d roosevelt planned war strategy from the ship harry 
truman used it for the first international conference on nuclear 
arms control and richard nixon held working sessions with the likes 
of soviet leader leonid brezhnev on board mcgehee said 
the ship was open for public visits over the weekend at the 
charlestown navy yard in boston it will make more stops along the 
atlantic coast before it is donated to the navy on nov 15 and 
again becomes the presidential yacht 
the fundraising voyage has raised 55 million half the 11 
million needed for restoration costs and to create an endowment for 
future maintenance and operations without taxpayer expense he said 
but mcgehee said reagan has failed to stamp his imprimatur on 
the project 
this is the ultimate private sector project he said one 
would think ronald reagan would be willing to hold this up and say 
this is what ive been talking about 
lyndon johnson used the lure of an afternoon cruise on the ship 
to entangle legislators in marathon discussions and hold them 
hostage until they came around to his point of view mcgehee said 
weve had some funny stories about senators and congressmen 
telling the captain to turn the boat around and go back to dock 
the captain would say he could only listen to his 
commanderinchief 
nixon enjoyed taking cruises on the potomac in the sequoia and 
announced his decision to resign the presidency to his family 
aboard the ship 
a joint congressional resolution in 1985 provided for the 
sequoias eventual return and the ship was designated a national 
historic landmark earlier this year 
mcgehee said the presidential yacht trust has spent 35 million 
restoring teak paneling bleached ash interiors handmade carpets 
engines and other details the ship was built for 210000 but to 
build it now would cost between 8 million and 10 million 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

