manatee county commissioners didnt like the bradenton dwarf 
toss but couldnt find a law under which they could ban it 
i think we all pretty much felt like it was lowlevel type of 
entertainment said commission chairman kent chetlain its 
like somebody capitalizing on someones disfigurement or 
infirmity 
animal house publicist richard levy brushed off such 
contentions saying the contest is fun attracts customers and is 
certain to generate publicity for the bar 
and wilson said he makes good money being tossed 
dwarftossing began as a bar stunt in queensland australia 
said van ettens wife angela author of dwarfs dont live in doll 
houses 
it is actually freak show entertainment the sort of thing you 
saw in the 1930s she said the problem with freak show 
entertainment is it sets the dwarf apart as something to be stared 
out and made fun of which makes it difficult for the rest of us 
who arent participating to be treated as equal 
